%N A395327 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of partitions of {1..3n} that are invariant under a permutation consisting of n 3-cycles with k orbits of blocks.
%H A395327 Alois P. Heinz, <a href="/A395327/b395327.txt">Rows n = 0..150, flattened</a>
%F A395327 E.g.f.: exp( y*((exp(3*x) - 1)/3 + exp(x) - 1 ) ).
%e A395327 Triangle begins:
%e A395327   1;
%e A395327   0,    2;
%e A395327   0,    4,      4;
%e A395327   0,   10,     24,      8;
%e A395327   0,   28,    128,     96,     16;
%e A395327   0,   82,    680,    880,    320,     32;
%e A395327   0,  244,   3664,   7440,   4480,    960,    64;
%e A395327   0,  730,  20104,  61208,  54880,  19040,  2688,  128;
%e A395327   0, 2188, 112368, 500416, 632576, 318080, 71680, 7168, 256;
%e A395327   ...
%e A395327 Case n=2: Without loss of generality the permutation of two 3-cycles can be taken as (123)(456). The T(2,1) = 4 set partitions that are invariant under this permutation with 1 orbit are {{1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}}, {{1, 4}, {2, 5}, {3, 6}}, {{1, 5}, {2, 6}, {3, 4}}, {{1, 6}, {2, 4}, {3, 5}}. The T(2,2) = 4 partitions with 2 orbits are {{1, 2, 3}, {4, 5, 6}}, {{1, 2, 3}, {4}, {5}, {6}}, {{1}, {2}, {3}, {4, 5, 6}}, {{1}, {2}, {3}, {4}, {5}, {6}}.
%p A395327 b:= proc(n) option remember; `if`(n=0, 1, add((1+
%p A395327       3^(j-1))*binomial(n-1, j-1)*expand(b(n-j)*x), j=1..n))
%p A395327     end:
%p A395327 T:= (n,k)-> coeff(b(n), x, k):
%p A395327 seq(seq(T(n,k), k=0..n), n=0..9);  # _Alois P. Heinz_, Apr 27 2026
%o A395327 (PARI) T(n) = {[Vecrev(p) | p<-Vec(serlaplace(exp( y*((exp(3*x + O(x*x^n)) - 1)/3 + exp(x + O(x*x^n)) - 1 ) )))]}
%o A395327 { my(A=T(8)); for(i=1, #A, print(A[i])) }
